message.content:
We start by extracting the key numbers from the three statements and then apply the standard formulas.

1. Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio (and Operating Cash Flow Ratio)  
 Formula: Operating Cash Flow ÷ Total Current Liabilities  
 • Operating Cash Flow from operating activities = –1,182,491.05  
 • Total Current Liabilities (end) = 499,821.72  
 Calculation: –1,182,491.05 ÷ 499,821.72 ≈ –2.37

2. Debt to Equity Ratio  
 Formula: Total Liabilities ÷ Total Owner’s Equity  
 Note: In this case the liabilities come entirely from current liabilities.  
 • Total Liabilities = 499,821.72  
 • Total Owner’s Equity (end) = 14,390,936.99  
 Calculation: 499,821.72 ÷ 14,390,936.99 ≈ 0.03

3. Total Asset Turnover Ratio  
 Formula: Total Revenue ÷ Total Assets  
 • Total Revenue = 3,956,433.90  
 • Total Assets (end) = 14,890,758.71  
 Calculation: 3,956,433.90 ÷ 14,890,758.71 ≈ 0.27

4. Quick Ratio  
 Formula: (Total Current Assets – Inventory) ÷ Total Current Liabilities  
 • Total Current Assets (end) = 9,982,261.98  
 • Inventory (end) = 0.00  
 • Total Current Liabilities = 499,821.72  
 Calculation: 9,982,261.98 ÷ 499,821.72 ≈ 19.96

5. (Again) Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
 This is the same as ratio (1) in this context: ≈ –2.37

6. Return on Equity (ROE)  
 We use the average owner’s equity in the period.  
 • Beginning owner’s equity = 13,000,000.00  
 • Ending owner’s equity = 14,390,936.99  
 Average Equity = (13,000,000.00 + 14,390,936.99) ÷ 2 = 13,695,468.50  
 • Net Profit = 1,390,936.99  
 Calculation: 1,390,936.99 ÷ 13,695,468.50 ≈ 0.1015, or 10.15%

7. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
 Formula: Total Revenue ÷ Average Accounts Receivable  
 • Accounts Receivable (beginning) = 0.00  
 • Accounts Receivable (end) = 3,149,338.94  
 Average Accounts Receivable = (0.00 + 3,149,338.94) ÷ 2 = 1,574,669.47  
 • Total Revenue = 3,956,433.90  
 Calculation: 3,956,433.90 ÷ 1,574,669.47 ≈ 2.51

Thus, the answers rounded to two decimals are:

{
  "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-2.37",
  "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.03",
  "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.27",
  "Quick Ratio": "19.96",
  "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-2.37",
  "Return on Equity (ROE)": "10.15%",
  "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "2.51"
}
